Mansur M wrote a review Jul 2021
India455 contributions38 helpful votes
+1
Great Location and Decor, Fantastic View of Ocean and Beach from Balcony
The hotel is located at the rightest location in Da Nang City, Plenty of street food stalls just at stone throw distance, Rooms with Ocean View Balcony are amazing, Breakfast is good and enough to choose from, Room Interior are unique specially the batroom shower enclosure in between the middle of room. BE CAREFUL OF BATH MIXTURE, Its get very hot and could burn your skin. Look for HOT sticker placed near the water regulator. Look at pictures attached to have a view of Room, balcony, Beach, The room entrance is through a huge living room with a tiny powder room and another Balcony with a cloth drying hanger trolley. Only one star less in my review because of damp smell inside room. everything else is unique.
Date of stay: July 2020
Stennius wrote a review Feb 2020
17 contributions6 helpful votes
Nice hotel next to the beach. Top infinity pool is tiny, but offers great possibilities to nice IG shots.
The location next to the beach is nice. Currently the next hotel is just constructing, and it causes a lot of noise which totally blocks balcony usage - and blocks all the view. And believe me, many hotels are a lot closer to each other than this approximately 20m distance. The road between the hotel and beach is just crazy. There are 4 lines to both directions. But don't rely on those directions, watch both ways before crossing! People are driving like lunatics in there. In our room there were two bedrooms, living room, kitchen and two bathrooms. Nice. Some fruits on the table when checked in. One 0.5l bottle of water every day as well as instant coffee and tea. In kitchen there were no forks, knives or pans and pots. I don't know who needs those on holidays, but kitchen‚Ä¶
