Traveler O wrote a review Feb 2020
Washington DC, District of Columbia1058 contributions540 helpful votes
Hotel on the Beachfront
Located right across the street from the beach, the location is solid and the hotel itself is a very good option to consider. Reserved a two bedroom, two bath room and it was worth it. There's an outdoor entertainment venue right across the street that's used almost nightly, so music/terrible karaoke/loud voices on mics will often go until about 2200 or so, then it normally quiets down. Just be aware of that. Room was spacious, breakfast spread in the restaurant was good (there's a kids playroom inside the restaurant), the lobby cafe was good too. Rooftop restaurant, bar, and pool was very nice. Great views of the area. There's also a spa on the floor just below the rooftop bar. Not far from the airport, plenty of restaurants nearby, free shuttles to Hoi An and surrounding‚Ä¶
Date of stay: September 2019
